  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 11.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The pots",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As stated above, the Hebrew word is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "הַסִּירות",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It occurs in the Old Testament twenty-seven times; it is translated in our Authorized Version \"pans\" once and \"caldrons\" four times. By a manifest copyist's error, the parallel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 7:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") has ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "כִירות",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"layers,\" by the use of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "caph",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "samech.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The use of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "סִיר",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " was to boil the peace offerings, though some say they were hods in which to carry away the ashes; and it certainly is remarkable that it is no one of the words employed in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 2:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In addition to these twenty-seven times, it occurs also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "four",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " times in Ecclesiastes, Isaiah, Hosed, Nahum, with the meaning of \"thorns,\" and once in Amos it is translated \"fish-hooks.\" The passage in Ecclesiastes (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ecclesiastes 7:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is additionally remarkable, in the fact that the root occurs twice in the same sentence in its different significations, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "e.g.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"the crackling of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "thorns",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " under a pot.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The shovels",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Hebrew word is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "הַיָעִים",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This word occurs in the Old Testament nine times - in Exodus, Numbers, Kings, Chronicles, and Jeremiah. The use of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "shovel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " was to remove the ashes. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The basins",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " should very probably read ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
